# bicep-textmate
Textmate grammar prototype for https://github.com/Azure/bicep

## Changing the grammar
* [`bicep.grammar.yml`](./bicep.grammar.yml) contains the textmate grammar - it's used to generate the JSON and PLIST style grammars.

## Tests
* Run the tests with:
    ```sh
    cd src/tests
    npm i
    npm test
    ```

## Previewing with VSCode
* Install dependencies:
    ```sh
    cd src/vscode-biceptm
    npm i
    ```
* In VSCode, select the **VSCode Textmate Test** [Run/Debug option](https://code.visualstudio.com/Docs/editor/debugging), and open a `.bicep` file in the new VSCode window that pops up. The [Scope Inspector](https://code.visualstudio.com/api/language-extensions/syntax-highlight-guide#scope-inspector) is helpful for debugging scoping rules.
